               <desc type="building-data">The Hall of the Three Transcendents (三仙殿) in Baiyu Palace is an axial building dating from the Ming-Qing dynasties [ZGWWDTJ, Shanxi vol 2 (zhong), p. 513 23-C10]  It has an overhanging gable roof, its front façade measures 8.56 m (28' 1") and its side facade measures 7.9 m (25' 11"). Entry by TM</desc>
